<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Yinka-odumakin-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&amp;ssl=1" alt="Buhari can’t be trusted on third tem plot – Afenifere" class="amp-wp-295b586"> Dayo Johnson – Akure The Pan Yoruba socio-political organization, Afenifere, on Tuesday asked Nigerians to be vigilant and ready to thwart any attempt by President Muhammadu Buhari to take the country for a ride on the purported third term agenda. Rising from its General Meeting held in Akure, the country home of its national leader, Reuben Fasoranti, the group advised the President to perish the thought of a third term in office. The National Publicity Secretary of the group, Yinka Odumakin, who read the group’s communiqué, said “we have seen this fire before for this smoke not to be strange to us. Continue reading Buhari can’t be trusted on third tem plot – Afenifere at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard